# =============================================================================
# Xenium Xcel Consult — environment variables for Vercel
# =============================================================================
# How to add on Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#   • Add each name/value, or paste multiple lines (Vercel accepts KEY=value format).
#   • Enable for Production (and Preview if you want forms to work on preview deploys).
#   • Redeploy after saving (Deployments → three dots → Redeploy).
# =============================================================================
# Do NOT commit a real .env with secrets to git. This file is a template only.
# =============================================================================

# ——— Resend (required for contact form + job application emails) ———
# Create at: https://resend.com/api-keys
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# "From" must use your verified domain (xeniumxcel.com is verified in Resend).
# Use any mailbox/alias you enable on that domain. Common choices:
#   noreply@xeniumxcel.com
#   hello@xeniumxcel.com
#   no-reply@xeniumxcel.com
# Display name is optional: Xenium Xcel Consult <address@xeniumxcel.com>
RESEND_FROM="Xenium Xcel Consult <noreply@xeniumxcel.com>"

# ——— Inbox: where ALL form emails are delivered (contact + job application) ———
FORMS_EMAIL=info@xeniumxcel.com

# ——— Site (recommended for sitemap, Open Graph, JSON-LD canonical URLs) ———
# No trailing slash. Must be NEXT_PUBLIC_* so the browser can read it.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.xeniumxcel.com

# ——— Optional fallbacks (only if you do NOT set FORMS_EMAIL above) ———
# APPLICATION_EMAIL=info@xeniumxcel.com
# CONTACT_EMAIL=info@xeniumxcel.com
